chat_messages.text:
 The cancel bug is here — your brush has two separate handlers:

```js
.on("brush", brushed)   // fires while dragging
.on("end", brushended)  // fires when released
```

When you **clear** the brush (click without dragging), only `brushended` fires with `selection: null`, which correctly sets `filter = []` and calls `update()`. That part is fine.

The real problem is that the `brush` object is created **once at module load time** with `.on("brush", brushed)` — but `brushed` closes over `xScale` which doesn't exist yet. More critically, the `$:` block that calls `d3.select(brushLayer).call(brush)` **re-calls the brush every time any reactive variable changes**, which resets the brush visual and can interfere with clearing.

The fix is to separate brush setup (once, in `onMount`) from axis updates (reactive):

```svelte
<script>
