 The issue is that `filter` is a prop exported from `Histogram.svelte`, and assigning to it inside the component doesn't automatically propagate back to the parent in Svelte — `bind:filter` only works reactively if the parent's variable is updated. When you do `filter = [...]` inside `onMount`, Svelte loses the binding context.

The fix is to stop assigning to `filter` directly inside the histogram and instead pass the range value through the `update` callback:

**In `Histogram.svelte`**, change `update` to accept the new filter value:

```js
.on("brush", (event) => {
    if (event.selection) {
        const newFilter = [
            xScale.invert(event.selection[0]),
            xScale.invert(event.selection[1])
        ];
        update(newFilter);  // pass value up
    }
})
.on("end", (event) => {
    if (!event.selection) {
        update([]);  // pass empty up
    }
});
```

**In `App.svelte`**, define three separate update functions that each set their own filter:

```js
function makeUpdater(filterSetter) {
    return function(newFilter) {
        filterSetter(newFilter);
        updateData();
    }
}
```

And pass them to each histogram:

```svelte
<Histogram
    data={data}
    fullData={fullData}
    variable={selectedVar}
    update={(f) => { filter1 = f; updateData(); }}
    title="WVS (10 items)"
/>
<Histogram
    data={data}
    fullData={fullData}
    variable={selectedVar + '_human'}
    update={(f) => { filter2 = f; updateData(); }}
    title="WVS (125 items)"
/>
<Histogram
    data={data}
    fullData={fullData}
    variable={selectedVar + '_llm'}
    update={(f) => { filter3 = f; updateData(); }}
    title="LLM (125 items)"
/>
```

And remove `bind:filter` and the `export let filter` prop entirely from both sides — it's no longer needed since the filter value flows through `update()` instead. Also update `updateData` to track filters internally:

```js
let filter1 = [], filter2 = [], filter3 = [];
```

These stay as plain `let` variables in `App.svelte`, just no longer bound to the histogram props.

