 Yes! The vertical lines are appearing because the histogram brush is setting `selectedCountries` to all countries in the filtered range. You probably only want the lines when a **specific country is clicked** on the map, not when a range brush is active.

The simplest fix is to track whether the selection came from a map/scatter click vs a histogram brush, and only show lines in the former case:

Add a flag in `App.svelte`:

```svelte
let selectionFromClick = false;

function handleMapClick(country) {
  selectionFromClick = true;
  // ... rest of your existing code
}

function handleBrushSelect(points) {
  selectionFromClick = true;
  // ... rest of your existing code
}

function updateData() {
  selectionFromClick = false;
  // ... rest of your existing code
}
```

Then pass it to each Histogram:

```svelte
<Histogram ... selectedCountries={selectionFromClick ? selectedCountries : new Set()} />
```

This way the vertical lines only appear when selection came from a map click or scatterplot brush, and disappear when the histogram brush is the active filter.

