\textbf{Issue-Specific Evolution: Sexuality}
The transformation of belief systems can be further illustrated through the case of attitudes toward homosexuality, using the item “Justifiable: Homosexuality” as an indicator (Figures~\ref{fig:sexuality_trend} and \ref{fig:sexuality_clusters}). This item was not asked in Waves 1 and 2. Figure~\ref{fig:sexuality_trend} shows the share of clusters at each wave in which the item appears as a defining characteristic. The x-axis represents the wave, and the y-axis the proportion of clusters. The figure highlights that the item first appears in Wave 3, peaks in Waves 3–4, declines in Wave 5, rises again in Wave 6, and reaches its lowest proportion in Wave 7. 
\begin{figure}[!h]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width = 12cm]{images/homosexuality_share_of_clusters.png}
    \caption{Share of cluster with 'Justifibaly: Homosexuality' as cluster-characterizing items accross seven waves}
    \label{fig:sexuality_trend}
\end{figure}
Figure~\ref{fig:sexuality_clusters} shows the average BC of the clusters in which the item is present. Each dot represents a cluster where the item is defining, colored by primary theme, and labeled with the full theme combination; the line indicates the item’s average centrality across clusters at each wave.
\begin{figure}[!h]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width = 12cm]{images/homosexuality_bc_trajectory_corrected.png}
    \caption{Cluster with 'Justifiable: Homosexuality' as important item across seven waves}
